{{{An Earth-Sheltered Home}}}

Imagine a house that’s more like a gentle hill on the landscape than a traditional building. This is an earth-sheltered home, designed to blend with and use the earth itself for protection and efficiency. Rather than having all four walls exposed to the wind and weather, it is built partially or entirely into a hillside or covered with soil and sod.

What makes it unique is its incredible natural insulation. The massive earth walls keep the interior temperature remarkably stable—cool in the blistering summer heat and warm during the freezing winter—dramatically reducing the need for conventional heating and air conditioning. It is also exceptionally quiet inside, as the earth muffles outside noise, and it has a very low environmental impact, often appearing as part of the natural terrain. For someone who has never seen one, picture a cozy, modern home hiding in plain sight within a grassy mound, with large windows typically facing the sun to fill the space with natural light.

